<|channel>thought
<channel|>冇問題，我明白晒。我會用道地嘅廣東話同埋你要求嘅格式嚟造句。

# 詞: 銀包

1. 我唔記得咗帶銀包，今次真係唔知點算好。 (I forgot to bring my wallet; I really don't know what to do now.)
2. 佢個銀包好厚，入面應該裝咗好多錢。 (His wallet is very thick; there must be a lot of money inside.)
3. 唔好意思，可唔可以借你個銀包，我想借啲錢出嚟？ (Excuse me, can I borrow your wallet? I want to take some money out.)
4. 我啱啱先至發現，原來我個銀包跌咗喺巴士上面。 (I just realized that I dropped my wallet on the bus.)
5. 呢個銀包嘅設計好靚，送畀女朋友做生日禮物啱晒。 (The design of this wallet is beautiful; it's perfect as a birthday gift for my girlfriend.)
6. 佢個銀包好細個，啱啱好可以放晒所有信用卡。 (Her wallet is very small; it can just fit all her credit cards.)
7. 你搵唔搵到個銀包呀？係咪擺咗喺件褸袋入面？ (Can you find your wallet? Is it in your jacket pocket?)
8. 我個銀包入面除咗錢之外，仲有一張好重要嘅身份證。 (Besides money, there is also an important ID card in my wallet.)
9. 佢買咗個名牌銀包，用咗好耐都仲係好新。 (He bought a designer wallet, and it still looks new even after long use.)
10. 唔好將銀包放喺褲袋最外面，咁樣好容易會畀人偷。 (Don't put your wallet in the outermost pocket of your pants; it's very easy to get stolen.) [end of text]


